commit_message:
Verify keystone connection using token

This patch simplifies the keystone connectivity check to just
get a token instead of making another call that internally gets
a token too. This ensures that only the public keystone endpoint
needs to be accesible, by contrast with the previous project or
region list that needed access to the admin keystone endpoint,
which is usually not accesible from within OpenStack VMs.

Closes-Bug: 1789632
Change-Id: Id19a7e7e1662c33dfb5df417ac24d22926227737
(cherry picked from commit 810865cad431a822b39f9a8f8f8637a277ce54e6)

commit_message:
Cleanup generation of rabbitmq server data

In the past, ansible_hostname could contain a FQDN or a hostname.
This is not the case anymore as fqdns are now stored in facts as
ansible_fqdn while short hostnames are stored in ansible_hostname.

This also simplifies the reading by using json_query.

Change-Id: I0755684846e42b4a17c4e46d70940535daaf73e7

commit_message:
Fix config_template to work with Ansible 2.6

In Ansible 2.6 the copy module now recognizes the "_original_basename"
option and not the "original_basename" option. In order for this module
to work with versions less than 2.6.0 and 2.6.0+ we need to allow an if
statement based on the version of Ansible being used.

Change-Id: I3f7a12dec77ea6e8e3c9fcae6ce9c162df57e50c
(cherry picked from commit fcf669b78c9266212a07a0a1caef6ff73a7cef73)

revisions:
[{'created': '2018-08-27 09:21:05.000000000', 'message': "Caching ResourceCollectionBase::get_members()

Right now each time 'get_members()' method gets called a new list
is created with fresh instantiation of element type resources.

This ought to be optimized by returning the cached result in
case of repetitive invocations and should the need be to fetch
the refreshed result it would ideally reinstantiate the member
resources of the collection. Also, in case of any member resource
element within collection is being marked as stale, this handles
properly to return the refresh'ed resource if that is accessed
through this 'get_members()' method of the referenced resource
collection instance:

    res_collection_inst.get_members()[any_index].some_attr

to access the current (or live) value of 'some_attr' w/o the need
of recreating (read re-instantiating) the constituent element
resource instance.

Change-Id: I7885143baa430d4e088f99febd6f8bc1a4f99aea
"}]
commit_message:
Caching ResourceCollectionBase::get_members()

Right now each time 'get_members()' method gets called a new list
is created with fresh instantiation of element type resources.

This ought to be optimized by returning the cached result in
case of repetitive invocations and should the need be to fetch
the refreshed result it would ideally reinstantiate the member
resources of the collection. Also, in case of any member resource
element within collection is being marked as stale, this handles
properly to return the refresh'ed resource if that is accessed
through this 'get_members()' method of the referenced resource
collection instance:

    res_collection_inst.get_members()[any_index].some_attr

to access the current (or live) value of 'some_attr' w/o the need
of recreating (read re-instantiating) the constituent element
resource instance.

Change-Id: I7885143baa430d4e088f99febd6f8bc1a4f99aea

commit_message:
Migration tests in v2.6 should not repeat all migration tests.

Now LiveMigrationRemoteConsolesV26Test inherits from
LiveMigrationTest, which will unnecessarily repeat all tests in
LiveMigrationTest. This is to change the v26 class inheritance
to save the running time.

Change-Id: I0929ad8a5ad5f1a4c2ae2d917e001c26aa9cec66

commit_message:
Maintenance: Add functional tests for database sync task

This patch is adding functional tests for the task responsible for
fixing the database. Currently the resources covered are: Networks,
ports, routers, subnets, security groups and security group rules (apart
from delete, bug listed inline).

Note that router ports and floating IPs are still missing and will be
submitted on subsequently patches.

Partial-bug: #1752897
Change-Id: If523d68b53229934f19c99f9bcca5128d78e482b
(cherry picked from commit f69b68d7d36c79bba211648acd5939ee3e52cd7a)

commit_message:
fix validation of stable branches for independent deliverables

The wrong variable was being used to check for the existing
branch. Add some debug messages to show what we do find and fix that
variable so the right branch name is checked.

Change-Id: I758f6aa3fd0b983af1b83a922b40c3181ae48014

commit_message:
Add project templates for openstack-tox-lower-constraints

Currently many projects use it [1] and in many cases adding requirement
of neutron or horizon. Currently there are other templates that covers
this need for horizon and neutron for other base jobs (e.g. py3*).

This patch adds the following templates for the
openstack-tox-lower-constraints job:

  - openstack-lower-constraints-jobs
  - openstack-lower-constraints-jobs-horizon
  - openstack-lower-constraints-jobs-neutron

[1]:
http://codesearch.openstack.org/?q=-%20openstack-tox-lower-constraints&i=nope&files=&repos=

Change-Id: Ied4fa97755941df31c228b1ec7d7fbecb7ddde66

commit_message:
Move the inspector boot management spec to backlog

When implementing this spec two critical problems were found:
* PXEBoot.validate requires instance image parameters, so we cannot
  use it during inspection.
* PXEBoot.prepare_ramdisk tries to configure DHCP/PXE environment,
  which clashes with inspector's one and requires VIFs to be present.

This change also marks the inspector part as done in 8.0.0 and
puts the unsolved problems into the text for anyone who will want
to revive the spec.

Finally, the RFE link is changed to storyboard.

Change-Id: I5a2920b1416889aaaed725e4cb669c505c2ed0bf

commit_message:
Always lowercase role name

Due to [1] ansible always access servers lowcase. Also, in respect to [2], this
patch lowercase name which is use in fqdn, hostname, ssh_known_hosts and other
places.

[1] https://github.com/ansible/ansible/pull/26850/commits/aa4278e5f3ac2fc70c18ebd2f135378fa76776c7
[2] https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc4343

Change-Id: Ib25832496d6504def436414b9c2903cbfe5854d4
Resolves: rhbz#1619556

commit_message:
import zuul job settings from project-config

This is a mechanically generated patch to complete step 1 of moving
the zuul job settings out of project-config and into each project
repository.

Because there will be a separate patch on each branch, the branch
specifiers for branch-specific jobs have been removed.

Because this patch is generated by a script, there may be some
cosmetic changes to the layout of the YAML file(s) as the contents are
normalized.

See the python3-first goal document for details:
https://governance.openstack.org/tc/goals/stein/python3-first.html

Change-Id: I59e0d04455f340fcbfe11f9d9bfdaccd9b5afd78
Story: #2002586
Task: #24337

commit_message:
doc: Additional fixes to the SR-IOV doc

- Add steps to ensure physnets VLAN ranges are configured, if necessary
- Add steps to ensure a network using the given physnet is configured
- Update nova scheduler options, which have been moved since Ocata
  (nova 15.0.0) [1]
- Simply some commands
- Some typo/grammar fixes

[1] https://github.com/openstack/nova/commit/7d0381c91a6

Change-Id: Ida499bda2cc6b91230cc6595b049fe62957d55a3
Signed-off-by: Stephen Finucane <sfinucan@redhat.com>

commit_message:
do not flush selection on "old" boot source

This fixes an issue introduced by watchers:
when page initialized images watchers called before
select boot source watcher.it leads to sutiation when
we specify selection from user input and flush it on
updateBootSource. as a result page come to
inconsistent state described in the bug.
Perhaps, this requires big refactoring but  in the
current patch we do not flush selection if boot type
was not changed. it allows to use image, snapshot,
volume from context as ctrl.selection.

Change-Id: I4b23071a2a9e2c02cc1f46713165e5cb5155894f
Closes-Bug: #1710890

commit_message:
import zuul job settings from project-config

This is a mechanically generated patch to complete step 1 of moving
the zuul job settings out of project-config and into each project
repository.

Because there will be a separate patch on each branch, the branch
specifiers for branch-specific jobs have been removed.

Because this patch is generated by a script, there may be some
cosmetic changes to the layout of the YAML file(s) as the contents are
normalized.

See the python3-first goal document for details:
https://governance.openstack.org/tc/goals/stein/python3-first.html

Change-Id: I7633d4a5f82075c427327b566828d8d789046538
Story: #2002586
Task: #24337

[{'created': '2018-08-30 13:14:49.000000000', 'message': 'build the redirects for the project-deploy-guide dynamically

Pass the list of maintained series to the template environment so we
can use that list to generate all of the redirects to the
project deploy guide pages instead of having to update the list of
series in two places.

The newton series is handled as a special case because it exists but
is not considered maintained.

commit_message:
build the redirects for the project-deploy-guide dynamically

Pass the list of maintained series to the template environment so we
can use that list to generate all of the redirects to the
project deploy guide pages instead of having to update the list of
series in two places.

The newton series is handled as a special case because it exists but
is not considered maintained.

Change-Id: I10794819260f1edd54e3711258ab715910ccf20f
Signed-off-by: Doug Hellmann <doug@doughellmann.com>

commit_message:
tests: Use 'ansible_connection=local' for connecting to localhost

Right now, Ansible tries to SSH to localhost and it fails if public
key authentication is not configured (eg. vagrant boxes). Since we
are running tests on localhost we may as well use 'local' as connection
type to avoid the unnecessary SSH connection.

Change-Id: I938afdcc7a1b47a1c0da0ab92ff73bbcd3afac27

commit_message:
Fix pep8 errors

Recent pep8 upgrade and corresponding pycodestyle update break
pep8 job due to the new rules.
- E402 module level import not at top of file
- E731 do not assign a lambda expression, use a def
- W503 line break before binary operator

progress, the jobs will be made voting and additional jobs will be added
for docs, api-ref, etc. Eventually the configuration will be update
to use templates.

The placement-core gerrit group will initially be seeded with the
existing nova-core group and a small number of additional people
selected from existing placement contributors.

The openstack/placement repo will initially be a part of the official
nova project. A patch indicating those plans will be made to governance.
It will depend on this change.

[1] https://git.openstack.org/cgit/openstack/oslo.tools/tree/filter_git_history.sh

commit_message:
Create an openstack/placement project

This patch includes the changes necessary to bootstrap an
openstack/placement repo that contains code seeded
from https://github.com/EdLeafe/placement . That repo contains
a clone of openstack/nova filtered by the filter_git_history.sh
script from oslo.tools [1]. The result is a collection of the
files that make up the placement service, it's test and docs
and auxilliary stuff. It is not a working repo. It will be
made to work via a series of changes to be reviewed in gerrit
once the new repo is seeded. Initially those changes will be
fairly mechanical, to fix file and import paths, and to remove
unneeded files that were included in the results because they
were non-placement members of commit required in the filtering.

The first commit will add a .zuul.yaml file that sets up some
noop-jobs and non-voting versions of openstack-tox-functional,
openstack-tox-functional-py35, openstack-tox-py27, openstack-tox-py35,
openstack-tox-p27, openstack-tox-pep8. As changes to the gerrit repo
progress, the jobs will be made voting and additional jobs will be added
for docs, api-ref, etc. Eventually the configuration will be update
to use templates.

The placement-core gerrit group will initially be seeded with the
existing nova-core group and a small number of additional people
selected from existing placement contributors.

The openstack/placement repo will initially be a part of the official
nova project. A patch indicating those plans will be made to governance.
It will depend on this change.

[1] https://git.openstack.org/cgit/openstack/oslo.tools/tree/filter_git_history.sh

Needed-By: https://review.openstack.org/598380
Change-Id: Icab8e931e5ae589eab0038ca12e6b5bdba04ff43

commit_message:
import zuul job settings from project-config

This is a mechanically generated patch to complete step 1 of moving
the zuul job settings out of project-config and into each project
repository.

Because there will be a separate patch on each branch, the branch
specifiers for branch-specific jobs have been removed.

Because this patch is generated by a script, there may be some
cosmetic changes to the layout of the YAML file(s) as the contents are
normalized.

See the python3-first goal document for details:
https://governance.openstack.org/tc/goals/stein/python3-first.html

Change-Id: Id985bb7bcc50e1286f5221612d3a4684c9824049
Story: #2002586
Task: #24314

commit_message:
Add ensure_lbaas_package to neutron::server

Adds a new parameter ensure_lbaas_package same as for the other
service provider plugins. This can be used to only install the
LBaaS package and not the agents so that the neutron-server can
load the plugin.

Change-Id: I7f074fe3f8d3935d18f640de0d8a256f39ea8b11
(cherry picked from commit c70e4fa7f29c4ea183e3dd8f54549a6a0643307b)

It adds the system storage resource of Redfish standard schema.
It represents the properties of a local storage controller with its
set of storage controllers (physical or virtual) and the resources
such as volumes that can be accessed from that subsystem. The
physical disk drives are also part of it.

It also provides the attribute ``max_volume_size_bytes`` &
``max_drive_size_bytes`` which give largest storage size available
in bytes among volumes and drives respectively.

Change-Id: If2b5114a04e2de91d3f126cd8a9af3c9c62837df

This new resource represents the properties of a storage subsystem

The storage volumes are built from physical disks managed by the
controllers.

This patch introduces the properties ``max_volume_size_bytes`` and
``max_drive_size_bytes`` of the Storage resource to expose the sizes
of the largest storage devices available to the System.

commit_message:
Add system storage resource support

Adds the system storage resource of Redfish standard schema.
This new resource represents the properties of a storage subsystem
that represents a set of storage resources consisting of storage
controllers (physical or virtual), volumes and physical disk drives.
The storage volumes are built from physical disks managed by the
controllers.

This patch introduces the properties ``max_volume_size_bytes`` and
``max_drive_size_bytes`` from the StorageCollection resource to
expose the sizes of the largest storage devices (volumes and drives)
available to the System.

Story: 1668487
Task: 12506

revisions:
[{'created': '2016-05-27 13:03:18.000000000', 'message': '[DO NOT MERGE] Health service plugin

Health service plugin implements health check execution support for all
plugins available in the neutron server. Health service plugin maintains
a list of available health checks.

When a health check execution is requested, the health service plugin
determines check implementation according to combination of resource name
and check name (when health of particular resource has been requested
using its ID), or a combination of collection name and check name (when
no ID has been specified). The actual diagnostics is delegated to the
health check implementation.

Other plugins are expected to inherit HealthCheckBaseInPlugin mixin
available from neutron/plugins/common/health.py. Unless customization of
health check search paths is required, it is the only change required to
enable other plugins support for health checking.

Common health check discovery functions are available both for plugins
and agents in neutron/common/health.py. These functions are used to
dynamically determine available health checks. The functions follow the
same pattern that is already used for dynamic loading of API extensions.

Related-Bug: 1507499
Change-Id: I564b8fb52db16f4a49c102b9ad350a13d7b6dc05
'}]
commit_message:
[DO NOT MERGE] Health service plugin

Health service plugin implements health check execution support for all
plugins available in the neutron server. Health service plugin maintains
a list of available health checks.

When a health check execution is requested, the health service plugin
determines check implementation according to combination of resource name
and check name (when health of particular resource has been requested
using its ID), or a combination of collection name and check name (when
no ID has been specified). The actual diagnostics is delegated to the
health check implementation.

Other plugins are expected to inherit HealthCheckBaseInPlugin mixin
available from neutron/plugins/common/health.py. Unless customization of
health check search paths is required, it is the only change required to
enable other plugins support for health checking.

Common health check discovery functions are available both for plugins
and agents in neutron/common/health.py. These functions are used to
dynamically determine available health checks. The functions follow the
same pattern that is already used for dynamic loading of API extensions.

Related-Bug: 1507499
Change-Id: I564b8fb52db16f4a49c102b9ad350a13d7b6dc05

commit_message:
Remove DATABASE_PASSWORD var

Given that those variables are defined and used by Devstack in its
initialize_database_backends function[1], it's not required to define
them. Otherwise, the instructions described in the process to setup
the environment for functional tests[2] cannot be completed.

[1] http://git.openstack.org/cgit/openstack-dev/devstack/tree/lib/database#n89
[2] http://docs.openstack.org/developer/neutron/devref/development.environment.html#id2

Change-Id: I8ea92dcbb2c195e14704d39fd579c4c579c2b554

redirecting the broken links

Some links are broken because of the doc migration.It is not acceptable to
manually test all links and fix them one by one. we can fix them all by
adding Apache redirect rules.

commit_message:
Add l3_agent to devstack/lib

This can be useful for VPNaaS [1], FWaaS [2] and other advance services.

[1] I0b86c432e4b2210e5f2a73a7e3ba16d10467f0f2
[2] neutron-fwaas/devstack/lib/l3_agent

Related-Bug: #1692128
Change-Id: I4a4a5961a5c1428938936db3816801c978addda9

commit_message:
Better handle l3-agent initialization failures

If the l3-agent is adding a new router and has a failure
during ri.process(), that router could be considered added,
even though it is not fully functional.  Any subsequent update
that arrives will not be able to fix this, as it will not be
able to re-do some of the initialization that should have been
done, such as adding the metadata redirect rules.

Instead, cleanup the router and schedule a resync so that
initialization can be re-tried.

Change-Id: Iae80ac57ce5f1fb5be59d761edc2e0d5ab9dd690
Closes-bug: #1735724

commit_message:
add 'ovs_interfaceid' to portbinding vif_details

Passing OVS interface id from neutron to nova is intended in [1]. And
this patch add new prameter 'ovs_interfaceid' to the 'vif_details' in
the portbinding API.

[1] https://review.openstack.org/#/c/19121/

Depends-On: I7d00f5ffe0b3504dcfd5d0be73f16c50b8b583d6

Signed-off-by: Ryota MIBU <r-mibu@cq.jp.nec.com>

detail might be different for each vif, depending to which network
it belongs to.

The current implementation had a big bug: If first a vif attached to

commit_message:
Ensure vif_details are unique per VIF

The Neutron framework assumes that the details of a vif are the same
cross all nics [1]. But with the macvtap agent they aren't! The vlan
detail might be different for each vif, depending to which network
it belongs to.

The current implementation had a big bug: If first a vif attached to
a vlan network was processed, the 'vlan' was stored in the instance
drivers self.vif_details variable. Now if after that a flat vif is
processed, self.vif_details did still contain the 'vlan' property.
The vif_details (including the vlan property) where sent over to
nova. Due to the 'vlan' property being present, nova was configuring
the macvtap with vlans, even though the vif belonged to a flat network.

The solution is to make a copy of self.vif_details each time we process
it.

[1] https://github.com/openstack/neutron/blob/7e3d6a18fb928bcd303a44c1736d0d6ca9c7f0ab/neutron/plugins/ml2/drivers/mech_agent.py#L142,L143

Change-Id: Id7134f933758ee768e13232af326423ac8c03c79
Closes-Bug: #1745159

Part II of Integrate Port OVO

This patch integrated Port OVO in db/db_base_plugin_common.py,
db/db_base_plugin_v2.py and some related files. Since Port is
a rather huge object to refactor, other remaining parts will
be addressed in following patches.

Partially-Implements: blueprint adopt-oslo-versioned-objects-for-db

commit_message:
Fix invalid dash search in fedora package

This commit fixes devstack when trying to install ovs dependencies. It
tries to install a non-existant kernel-foo package as the is_fedora flag
on devstack doesn't differenciate on Fedora/CentOS/... and currently
this was failing with Fedora 26.

Change-Id: Ibb10f3dbf8370f96e6a5edc2675e06780ab35a28
Closes-Bug: #1716963

commit_message:
Expand get-me-a-network to support any network topology

Improves auto-allocated topology functionality to support
three configuration types: 'auto', 'fixed', and 'circular',
which are set by the admin in the config file.

The admin creates specific networks and gives them the tag
'__auto-allocatable'. Then, if 'fixed' or 'circular' is chosen,
one of these networks is shared with the tenant when the tenant
auto-allocates a network. 'fixed' assigns only one tenant per
network, while 'circular' can assign multiple tenants to each
network if necessary. 'auto' is the same as the previous
functionality, creating a network, subnet, and router.

Related-bug: 1690438

Change-Id: Ie8296055468bbe76b527a57a5fbbb1807ed20139

[{'created': '2017-12-05 19:26:37.000000000', 'message': 'Fix delete_network() to do BEFORE and PRECOMMIT better

First, move segment deletion back to PRECOMMIT_DELETE, which
reverts commit 12d24abba75ab3b926edbac389437bacc23914dd,
"Delete segments on BEFORE_DELETE instead of PRECOMMIT".

Making the callback _delete_segments_for_network respond to
BEFORE_DELETE network event has created some bugs. In one of
them, it is not possible to delete a routed network, because
the segments cannot be deleted due to the fact that the
associated subnets still exist.

Making _delete_segments_for_network respond to PRECOMMIT_DELETE
introduces a StaleDataError with the standard attributes of the
deleted segments. To work around that, network_db is expired and
read again after notifying the PRECOMMIT_DELETE event in
delete_network in the DB core plug-in.

Second, create a BEFORE notifier in external_net_db to check if
there are associated floating IPs, so it can fail before we try
and delete the network.  The existing BEFORE notifier can then
be moved to PRECOMMIT.

Third, make _ensure_network_not_in_use() a BEFORE notifier,
since that better fits the design of how it is being used.

Closes-Bug #1697324
Closes-Bug #1732543

Change-Id: I5360847769120e4366629223ca5f93406ef9beb0
'}]
commit_message:
Fix delete_network() to do BEFORE and PRECOMMIT better

First, move segment deletion back to PRECOMMIT_DELETE, which
reverts commit 12d24abba75ab3b926edbac389437bacc23914dd,
"Delete segments on BEFORE_DELETE instead of PRECOMMIT".

Making the callback _delete_segments_for_network respond to
BEFORE_DELETE network event has created some bugs. In one of
them, it is not possible to delete a routed network, because
the segments cannot be deleted due to the fact that the
associated subnets still exist.

Making _delete_segments_for_network respond to PRECOMMIT_DELETE
introduces a StaleDataError with the standard attributes of the
deleted segments. To work around that, network_db is expired and
read again after notifying the PRECOMMIT_DELETE event in
delete_network in the DB core plug-in.

Second, create a BEFORE notifier in external_net_db to check if
there are associated floating IPs, so it can fail before we try
and delete the network.  The existing BEFORE notifier can then
be moved to PRECOMMIT.

Third, make _ensure_network_not_in_use() a BEFORE notifier,
since that better fits the design of how it is being used.

Closes-Bug #1697324
Closes-Bug #1732543

Change-Id: I5360847769120e4366629223ca5f93406ef9beb0

In order to not delete the networksegments entry for a network,
we must check the network is not in use before issuing the
BEFORE_DELETE notification.

As a side-effect, this could trigger a false-positive if it
is an external network and there are associated floating IPs
configured on it - the notification code can only deal with
un-associated floating IPs.  So we must check for that condition
before calling the BEFORE_DELETE notifiers.

Change-Id: I29bbee96dc88fb277db597a2467e18954d8782a1
Closes-bug: #1732543
'}]
commit_message:
Fail early deleting network

In order to not delete the networksegments entry for a network,
we must check the network is not in use before issuing the
BEFORE_DELETE notification.

As a side-effect, this could trigger a false-positive if it
is an external network and there are associated floating IPs
configured on it - the notification code can only deal with
un-associated floating IPs.  So we must check for that condition
before calling the BEFORE_DELETE notifiers.

Change-Id: I29bbee96dc88fb277db597a2467e18954d8782a1
Closes-bug: #1732543

commit_message:
import zuul job settings from project-config

This is a mechanically generated patch to complete step 1 of moving
the zuul job settings out of project-config and into each project
repository.

Because there will be a separate patch on each branch, the branch
specifiers for branch-specific jobs have been removed.

Because this patch is generated by a script, there may be some
cosmetic changes to the layout of the YAML file(s) as the contents are
normalized.

See the python3-first goal document for details:
https://governance.openstack.org/tc/goals/stein/python3-first.html

Change-Id: I9ad73265adc673d4ec4f7d412081e07c2cf55715
Story: #2002586
Task: #24337

commit_message:
Add config option endpoint_type for designate

Designate client uses publicURL as default endpoint type, add this
config to use internalURL as endpoint type.
The options of this config are as following in neutron.conf under
[designate]:
     endpoint_type=internalURL or endpoint_type=publicURL

Closes-bug: #1756291

Change-Id: Ibe3de32b6a6e322d8f77b87ade52af40acef340b

commit_message:
ovsfw: Remove add_protocols call

ovsfw is using OF1.0 and the native of_interface has been permitting
OF1.0 for quite some time. Remove this redundant call.

Change-Id: Ibd84cbfa00ac3c1feb77f3464369e28f90e899bc

Thank you for your first contribution to OpenStack.

    Your patch will now be tested automatically by OpenStack testing frameworks
    and once the automatic tests pass, it will be reviewed by other friendly
    developers. They will give you feedback and may require you to refine it.

    People seldom get their patch approved on the first try, so don't be
    concerned if requested to make corrections. Feel free to modify your patch
    and resubmit a new change-set.

    Patches usually take 3 to 7 days to be reviewed so be patient and be
    available on IRC to ask and answer questions about your work. Also it
    takes generally at least a couple of weeks for cores to get around to
    reviewing code. The more you participate in the community the more
    rewarding it is for you. You may also notice that the more you get to know
    people and get to be known, the faster your patches will be reviewed and
    eventually approved. Get to know others and become known by doing code
    reviews: anybody can do it, and it's a great way to learn the code base.

    Thanks again for supporting OpenStack, we look forward to working with you.

    IRC: https://wiki.openstack.org/wiki/IRC
    Workflow: http://docs.openstack.org/infra/manual/developers.html

Hello Jiaping,

I noticed you had submitted your first patch to OpenStack! Congratulations! I just wanted to reach out and follow up with you on the comments on your patch to see if you need any help. We want to help you get your patch merged and help you be successful in our community!\xa0

I've added some First Contact SIG contacts (neutron devs) to this patch. They will be able to review and help get the patch moving and get you connected.

Please let us know if you have any questions about your patch, the review process, or the community itself.\xa0

Hope to hear from you soon,\xa0

Matt and the rest of the First Contact SIG"}, {'account_id': 11975, 'date': '2018-05-09 08:01:19.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1

My only worry with the current code is there is a lot of possibility to have threads interfere with one another.'}, {'account_id': 28182, 'date': '2018-05-14 09:03:38.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 2.'}, {'account_id': 28182, 'date': '2018-05-15 06:53:50.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2:

(2 comments)

> Were you going to investigate using the queue model the l3-agent
 > uses?  My only worry with the current code is there is a lot of
 > possibility to have threads interfere with one another.

Thanks for the review. What do you mean about threads interfere?
I have tried using queues like l3-agent and it works too, but I think it will make the dhcp agent more complicated. Dhcp agent has used _wait_if_syncing decorator and net_lock to deal each message.So my idea is to minimize the change of code and control the process.'}, {'account_id': 11975, 'date': '2018-08-31 07:41:25.000000000', 'content': "Abandoned

commit_message:
Use eventlet greenpool to handle notification event for dhcp agent

If a lot of notification event messages are sent to dhcp agent at
the same time, especially port.update.end notification event, it
will result in a very high CPU load for the machine of dhcp agent.

So use eventlet greenpool to control concurrency of notification
event handling.

Change-Id: Ic47d4b8f5ad0ba65bc7fe7c076b268e78eb5fcc9
Closes-Bug: #1766812

[{'created': '2016-08-05 14:33:42.000000000', 'message': "Avoid apply firewall if remote sg members update

With ipset, When a local agent receives security_groups_member_updated
RPC with remote agent ports, it should only update ipset and shouldn't
reload iptables. This is alternate approach for [1].

In this patch, for security_groups_member_updated RPC, we won't reload
iptables(for both local and remote agent's ports).
When local agent's port security groups are updated, agent will get
port update notification and will reload iptables as part of rpc_loop
processing.

note: working on unit tests

[1] https://review.openstack.org/#/c/122368

Closes-bug: #1371435
Change-Id: Iab92cd19bb14c85f4dddb06ed396f039b16f2e08

commit_message:
Avoid apply firewall if remote sg members update

With ipset, When a local agent receives security_groups_member_updated
RPC with remote agent ports, it should only update ipset and shouldn't
reload iptables. This is alternate approach for [1].

In this patch, for security_groups_member_updated RPC, we won't reload
iptables(for both local and remote agent's ports).
When local agent's port security groups are updated, agent will get
port update notification and will reload iptables as part of rpc_loop
processing.

As we are not reloading iptables for remote sg members update,
l2 agent's rpc_loop will finish faster.

[1] https://review.openstack.org/#/c/122368

Co-Authored-By:shihanzhang <shihanzhang@huawei.com>
Closes-bug: #1371435
Closes-bug: #1499177
Change-Id: Iab92cd19bb14c85f4dddb06ed396f039b16f2e08

commit_message:
Do not turn-off IPv6 forwarding in HA routers if enabled

Changing the value of the IPv6 "all.forwarding" sysctl parameter
will cause an MLDv2 Leave to be sent to indicate we are no longer
a router, but this is unnecessary on an HA router since the
master will have sent a Join to update any upstream router
already.

If we then transition to master and IPv6 forwarding needs to
be enabled, then we must toggle the value to zero and back to 1
so that a Join will be sent. The extra Leave should not cause
any issues.

Related-Bug: #1771841

Change-Id: I5f74a996c92fd69da383baf3c3afe7160f4e5bc8

commit_message:
Revert "DVR: Fix allowed_address_pair IP, ARP table update by neutron agent"

This reverts commit fbe308bdc12191c187343b5ef103dea9af738380.

Will revert this commit, since the GARP is not reaching other DVR routers,
then the local one, to update the ARP entry all router namespaces.
This makes the situation worse rather than better.

More details can be found in bug #1773999

Closes-Bug: #1773999

Change-Id: I34c3458668ba0d9eb5e605b3ad0257903b952436

commit_message:
Enabling attach subports without specifying segmentation type and id

This patch implements the support for making SEGMENTATION-TYPE and
SEGMENTATION-ID optional for trunk-add-subport according to the
spec[1]:
"SEGMENTATION-TYPE and SEGMENTATION-ID are optional in both
trunk-create and trunk-subport-add in the generic case, allowing
neutron server to choose the type and id if needed."

The proposed change makes it not mandatory to have to specify the type
and the id, similarly to how IPs are selected right now when creating
a port. If a segmentation_type and segmentation_id are provided, they
are used as before. However, if no segmentation info is provided, the
default one (in this case the only one available: vlan) is used,
and an available segmentation_id within the defined interval is chosen.
Note there is a random shuffle among the available segmentation
ids to reduce collision probability as well as to speed up the
segmentation_id search.

[1] https://specs.openstack.org/openstack/neutron-specs/specs/newton/vlan-aware-vms.html#proposed-change

Change-Id: I093e1cc1b6ba2b8227ecbe9a8cb57f57096252f4

(1 comment)

As I commented in the bug report, my understanding is that  we cannot create subnet pools whose IP address range overlaps in a whole address scope so we can allow non-admin project to create a subnet pool from a shared address scope. However, I am not sure there is a reason we have the current behavior (only admin can create a subnet pool under a shared address scope). We need eyes from folks familiar with the L3 area.'}, {'account_id': 9423, 'date': '2017-06-15 13:00:37.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2: Published edit on patch set 1'}, {'account_id': 7718, 'date': '2017-06-15 13:10:56.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2:

Just wondering as per the existing behavior, if other tenants cannot create subnetpools in shared address scope then whats the predominant usecase shared addresscope is targeting? also as Akihiro said , uniqueness of IP will be ensured within the address scope, so not sure why we have to disallow this.'}, {'account_id': 20330, 'date': '2017-06-15 14:43:44.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2:

commit_message:
Allow subnetpool association with any shared address-scope

A tenant user should be able to associate owned subnetpool with
any shared address-scope.

Closes-Bug: #1697925
Change-Id: I6a20aaf10490e595bcc3f2d39cee99479478976e

commit_message:
ovsfw: Fix occasional network interruption with mark=1 in conntrack

If SG rules change on a port, SG flows on this port will be recreated.
Although all SG flows for this port will be added into OvS flows by
command 'ovs-ofctl add-flows' one-off, but flows will actually be
added into OvS flows one by one.
If there is a packet from outside to VM pass OvS flows when
'set mark=1' flows matched before SG rules flows added.
This will make mark=1 in conntrack for this kind packets and
result is that the establish-reply packets will be blocked.
It's the same situation for packets from VM to outside.

This patch will move 'set mark=1' flows after SG rules flows added
to avoid this issue.

Closes-Bug: #1719769

Change-Id: Ibd122bef53317d58d01119ed77488fbf5399d55a

Thank you for your first contribution to OpenStack.

    Your patch will now be tested automatically by OpenStack testing frameworks

    developers. They will give you feedback and may require you to refine it.

    People seldom get their patch approved on the first try, so don't be
    concerned if requested to make corrections. Feel free to modify your patch
    and resubmit a new change-set.

    Patches usually take 3 to 7 days to be reviewed so be patient and be
    available on IRC to ask and answer questions about your work. Also it
    takes generally at least a couple of weeks for cores to get around to
    reviewing code. The more you participate in the community the more
    rewarding it is for you. You may also notice that the more you get to know
    people and get to be known, the faster your patches will be reviewed and
    eventually approved. Get to know others and become known by doing code
    reviews: anybody can do it, and it's a great way to learn the code base.

    Thanks again for supporting OpenStack, we look forward to working with you.

commit_message:
ml2: make _device_to_port_id more robust

That method responsible to extract for a device string the port id has
been reworked to ensure that full port UUID is going to be returned or
raise a exception.

Co-Authored-By: Nate Johnston <nate.johnston@redhat.com>
Change-Id: Iee03e8fd808ea8237604454f4af5459d9fa156ee

commit_message:
Netlink driver to manage conntrack entries

This patch proposes ConntrackNetlink driver to delete conntrack
entries. Adopt Netlink solution [1] will improve conntrack
management performance.

[1] https://goo.gl/SrsA8z

Closes-Bug: #1630832
Co-Authored-By: Cao Xuan Hoang <hoangcx@vn.fujitsu.com>
Co-Authored-By: Slawek Kaplonski <skaplons@redhat.com>
Change-Id: Ib02e4768b5af0915d9f11cd1ef66a73b06a611f0

commit_message:
Implement basic policy module in code

This commit will prepare for implementing policies in code [1].

Like oslo.config, with oslo.policy, we can define all of
default rules in code base and only change some rules
via policy file. Another thing that we should use yaml
format instead of json format.

[1] https://governance.openstack.org/tc/goals/queens/policy-in-code.html

Change-Id: Ib8320c6919705f514d57ebcaf1218e72da393b69
Co-authored-By: Hieu LE <hieulq@vn.fujitsu.com>

[{'created': '2018-07-13 18:51:15.000000000', 'message': 'Use existing value for policy enforcement on PUTs

The Neutron policy enforcement code currently uses the new value
of an attribute (on a PUT request) to validate access to that
same attribute. The reason it does that is because it must specify
a key-value pair for the policy enforcement code to judge whether
or not the role has access to modify it. However, instead of putting
the new value in that key-value pair, it should be using the existing
value fetched from the database, if it exists. If it does not exist,
the key-value pair should be generated and put into the resource
object being modified before the object is passed to the policy
engine. Then after the policy engine validates access successfully,
the object attribute should be given the new value to be put into
the database.

Closes-Bug: #1779003

commit_message:
Use existing value for policy enforcement on PUTs

The Neutron policy enforcement code currently uses the new value
of an attribute (on a PUT request) to validate access to that
same attribute. The reason it does that is because it must specify
a key-value pair for the policy enforcement code to judge whether
or not the role has access to modify it. However, instead of putting
the new value in that key-value pair, it should be using the existing
value fetched from the database, if it exists. If it does not exist,
the key-value pair should be generated and put into the resource
object being modified before the object is passed to the policy
engine. Then after the policy engine validates access successfully,
the object attribute should be given the new value to be put into
the database.

Change-Id: I0c03a66668857ae64af348c75d9a61059c08b058
Closes-Bug: #1779003

commit_message:
import zuul job settings from project-config

This is a mechanically generated patch to complete step 1 of moving
the zuul job settings out of project-config and into each project
repository.

Because there will be a separate patch on each branch, the branch
specifiers for branch-specific jobs have been removed.

Because this patch is generated by a script, there may be some
cosmetic changes to the layout of the YAML file(s) as the contents are
normalized.

See the python3-first goal document for details:
https://governance.openstack.org/tc/goals/stein/python3-first.html

Change-Id: I1d81c1b136ddc79c0470fb5dedbdcc2f1c83f636
Story: #2002586
Task: #24298

commit_message:
Pin fog-openstack library to avoid breakage

The update of the fog-openstack ruby gem from 0.12.7 to 0.2.0 breaks
Chef recipes. The first call to cookbook-openstackclient from
cookbook-openstack-identity:recipes/registration.rb fails already with
something like (extract from a kitchen run of openstack-chef-repo):

  ERROR: openstack_domain[default] (openstack-identity::registration line 69)
  had an error: Fog::Identity::OpenStack::NotFound: Expected([200]) <=>
  Actual(404 Not Found)

  (http://127.0.0.1:35357/v3/v3/domains): The resource could not be found.

Change-Id: I4d30cb1770b6774b39bfd4e4c413f25816b405df

This patchset changes expected_error_codes behavior [0] by checking

commit_message:
Limit exception handling to calls within override_role

Motivation: prevents false positives caused by test
exceptions matching the expected exception before or
after the ``override_role`` context is called.

This patchset changes expected_error_codes behavior [0] by checking
errors explicitly outside the override_role context. This is done
by introducing a new function to rbac_rule_validation that is
used for validating that the expected exception isn't raised too
early (before ``override_role`` call) or too late (after
``override_call``) or at all (which is a bad test).

This means that exceptions raised prior to override_role
call result in failure. The same goes for exceptions raised
after override_role -- except for those that are an instance
of BasePatroleException (which is valid for things like
RbacMalformedResponse getting raised intentionally).

The new exception that is introduced is called
RbacOverrideRoleException.

Unit tests are added for all validation scenarios described
above.

Task: 24246

Co-Authored-By: Felipe Monteiro <felipe.monteiro@att.com>
Change-Id: Iae9a58640463093f6dda20d40261b20051be2820

commit_message:
Verify keystone connection using token

This patch simplifies the keystone connectivity check to just
get a token instead of making another call that internally gets
a token too. This ensures that only the public keystone endpoint
needs to be accesible, by contrast with the previous project or
region list that needed access to the admin keystone endpoint,
which is usually not accesible from within OpenStack VMs.

Closes-Bug: 1789632
Change-Id: Id19a7e7e1662c33dfb5df417ac24d22926227737

commit_message:
switch documentation job to new PTI

This is a mechanically generated patch to switch the documentation
jobs to use the new PTI versions of the jobs as part of the
python3-first goal.

See the python3-first goal document for details:
https://governance.openstack.org/tc/goals/stein/python3-first.html

Change-Id: I5693dcf746ef6b30ae3c33efbec666cccbc8e0ef
Story: #2002586
Task: #24296

commit_message:
Remove rootwrap.conf file from setup.cfg

https://review.openstack.org/527425 removed etc/rootwrap.conf, but
it did not remove its entry on setup.cfg. Thus, any attempt to do
"python setup.py install" will fail.

Change-Id: I041551fb6efb8fd52ff1eaa55f6b4af6738c4ded

commit_message:
Fix passphrase None errors

At this moment if ca_private_key_passphrase is None loadbalancer
cannot be created due to AttributeError.
Current change adds check for None before encoding.

Story: 2003588

Task: 24896

Change-Id: I40063aa2f96534c12b284f72d16c9f5a72ad1486

commit_message:
Prevents deletion of ports for active nodes

Prevents deletion of ironic port of the node whose provision
state is active. User can delete the port of such node's when
the node's are in the maintenance mode.

Co-Authored-By: Kaifeng Wang <kaifeng.w@gmail.com>
Change-Id: I3c2cc8ec5ddb04d7ab829d1341a045da6dee07e3
Closes-Bug: #1694693

resolve this.

[{'created': '2016-06-13 17:14:56.000000000', 'message': "Add RBAC for all referrers

Along with referrer access this change expands
RBAC for more combinations as allowed by SWIFT
ACL

Permission	                                    Read ACL options
Read and list for all referrers	                .r:*
Read and list for a user in a specific project  <project_id>:<user_id>
Read and list for a user in every project	    *:<user_name|user_id>
Read and list for every user in a project	    <project_id>:<*>
Read and list for every user in every project	<*>:<*>

Note:

  .rlistings doesn't need filter, since it can be achieved by
  requesting object name field 'only' in the query result, provided
  user has access

  *:* and .r:* are treated same in Searchlight as SL doesn't allow access
  without auth token as in the case of .r:*.

Change-Id: I43b1cb5238a8dcd3f2829ab59b188812543edd68
Closes-Bug: #1572747

commit_message:
Add RBAC for all referrers

Along with referrer access this change expands
RBAC for more combinations as allowed by SWIFT
ACL

Permission	                                Read ACL options
Read and list for all referrers	                .r:*
Read and list for a user in a specific project  <project_id>:<user_id>
Read and list for a user in every project	*:<user_id>
Read and list for every user in a project	<project_id>:<*>
Read and list for every user in every project	<*>:<*>

Note:

  .rlistings doesn't need filter, since it can be achieved by
  requesting object name field 'only' in the query result, provided
  user has access

  *:* and .r:* are treated same in Searchlight as SL doesn't allow access
  without auth token as in the case of .r:*.

Change-Id: I43b1cb5238a8dcd3f2829ab59b188812543edd68
Closes-Bug: #1572747

I spoke to Graham earlier and he mentioned that the parent/child relationship may be overkill here. Pools are an implementation detail of sharding zones across multiple DNS providers so although one might want to know the zones contained within a pool it's not likely queries would get more complex than that.

In addition, pools should be an admin-only entity (they're not initialized through regular API calls but instead through the equivalent of searchlight-manage) and this creates access problems in a parent/child relationship.

Also needs tests."}, {'account_id': 8959, 'date': '2016-06-17 19:59:55.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 3.'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2016-06-17 20:07:08.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3: Verified+1

commit_message:
Add pools to Designate plugin

Nameservers are not being indexed in designate plugin.
Pools is a new concept which will allow grouping of
namesevers to which a zone could be allocated to.
Zones are allocated to a pool based on attributes
which are selected by the appropriate filter.

For updating pools see
http://docs.openstack.org/developer/designate/pools.html

Change-Id: I6ed8a2060b5ef061e3ddb47ceb616d7ed513b10f
Closes-Bug: #1563497

commit_message:
WIP Policy rbac DO NOT MERGE

Postponing until after Newton/indefinitely. It's apparent that the
various services treat policy files differently; glance's allows
everything but filters in code, and neutron's is more complete. We may
need to rethink the approach a bit but it's too late in the release now.

This is very very WIP (and isn't plumbed in yet) but it demonstrates
turning policy checks into RBAC rules. The intent is to replace the
default RBAC queries with policy-based ones if present.

Change-Id: Ia46dbe4ecfaa3b49bdc08d61cc6ad6085415e26e

(1 comment)

Don't think the pipe is necessary but otherwise looks ok. What's the specific reason for making this change? .pyo files won't be created unless you modify something to run with -O"}, {'account_id': 20761, 'date': '2016-09-16 15:49:15.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

yes you are Right pipe is not necessary but i think this change need to be done in code because if you change somthing and run with -o then -pyo object will be created .'}, {'account_id': 14680, 'date': '2016-10-05 22:21:26.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1

I agree that the "|" should be removed. But I have larger concerns.

What is the justification for this change? Is there a bug report we can reference? We do not create optimized python files in Searchlight. Someone would have to go out of their way to enable this.

Also, *.py0 files went away in Python 3.5 [1][2]. So is this still an issue?

If we do make this change, we should also modify .gitignore to ignore *.pyo files (e.g. replacing the line "*.pyc" with "*.py[co]".

[1] https://www.python.org/downloads/release/python-352/
[2] https://www.python.org/dev/peps/pep-0488/'}, {'account_id': 27068, 'date': '2018-08-31 06:48:31.000000000', 'content': 'Abandoned'}]

It may be me being pedantic, but neither systemctl or the dnsmasq pxe filter is firewall based. Since the file with the filters for iptables have *firewall* in it's name I think adding non-firewall related things there confusing."}, {'account_id': 24828, 'date': '2018-08-21 02:41:24.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

> > I wonder why not add systemctl to the existing ironic-inspector-firewall.filters?
 > 
 > It may be me being pedantic, but neither systemctl or the dnsmasq

 > iptables have *firewall* in it's name I think adding non-firewall
 > related things there confusing.

Ok, I think that make sense, but I also feel "-systemctl" is a bit narrow here. Since we group commands into one file logically, do you think "-utils" could be a suitable one?'}, {'account_id': 24245, 'date': '2018-08-21 07:21:02.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

> > > I wonder why not add systemctl to the existing
 > ironic-inspector-firewall.filters?
 > >
 > > It may be me being pedantic, but neither systemctl or the dnsmasq
 > > pxe filter is firewall based. Since the file with the filters for
 > > iptables have *firewall* in it's name I think adding non-firewall
 > > related things there confusing.
 > 
 > Ok, I think that make sense, but I also feel "-systemctl" is a bit
 > narrow here. Since we group commands into one file logically, do
 > you think "-utils" could be a suitable one?

Yes, I think using one file would make sense. We could even just name it ironic-inspector.filters? (Comparing to other projects, nova uses few files with many filters in each file, Compute.filter, Network.filter etc.) 

Wonder if renaming the ironic-inspector-firewall.filters and addubg the filter rules there is the way to go? I am a bit unsure because it might break some packaging projects.)'}, {'account_id': 24828, 'date': '2018-08-21 09:11:17.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

I find rpm spec is fairly stable, and according to current implementation, I think it may have no impact on packaging:

   install -p -D -m 640 rootwrap.d/* %{buildroot}/%{_sysconfdir}/ironic-inspector/rootwrap.d/

I am not sure about other platform though, but I think that's the focus of packaging team?"}, {'account_id': 24245, 'date': '2018-08-21 09:44:49.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 2.'}, {'account_id': 24245, 'date': '2018-08-21 09:46:43.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 2:

 > 
 > I am not sure about other platform though, but I think that's the
 > focus of packaging team?

Thanks Kaifeng. I pushed another revision proposing to add the filter to the existing file, and rename it to give it a generic name unrelated to the actual commands in the filters."}, {'account_id': 24828, 'date': '2018-08-21 11:10:38.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2: Code-Review+1

commit_message:
Add rootwrap filter for systemctl control of dnsmasq

The dnsmasq pxe filter takes start/stop commands for the
dnsmasq service as options. Restarting the systemd service
requries root access.

This change adds a rootwrap filter to allow systemctl
control of the dnsmasq service.

NOTE: The systemd service name is the one used in the RDO
distribution. Additional filters may be needed for other
distributions.

Story: 2002818
Task: 24754
Change-Id: Ie961ec4d3b6b65a462e2d2493f5b9240c2bfa7a6

commit_message:
Add http_proxy_to_wsgi to api-paste

This sets up the HTTPProxyToWSGI middleware in front of searchlight.
The purpose of this middleware is to set up the request URL correctly in
case there is a proxy in front of searchlight.

The HTTPProxyToWSGI is off by default and needs to be enabled via a
configuration value.

Change-Id: Idb825af72a13baecd84f40675c1743f12c42d2b3

  existing@openstack platfrom

  tests.functional.utils.Rally .

[{'created': '2018-08-30 06:14:08.000000000', 'message': 'wheel-index: only create index once

We saw what looks very much like the index generation racing, with
"mv" unable to close the index file ...

Move to a linear strategy so that each host finishes each task before
moving on.  Then add run_once to the index generation so only one of
the hosts in a python2/3 situation creates the index file.

Change-Id: I3761dd9d2ab752e66bcccdd2434405f11535b95f
'}]
commit_message:
wheel-index: only create index once

We saw what looks very much like the index generation racing, with
"mv" unable to close the index file ...

Move to a linear strategy so that each host finishes each task before
moving on.  Then add run_once to the index generation so only one of
the hosts in a python2/3 situation creates the index file.

Change-Id: I3761dd9d2ab752e66bcccdd2434405f11535b95f

commit_message:
Adds more validations in create_snapshot

This patch adds more validations in create snapshot, like
host and replication. And removes the check logic
in create_snapshot_in_db method.

Change-Id: I8e5c7664e54116cc9e302e5e7903f4d7b04c836c

commit_message:
help: added dot at the end of base-arch description

--base-arch option has a list of allowed options listed after help description.

Without change:

  --base-arch BASE_ARCH
                        The base architecture. Default is same as host Allowed
                        values: x86_64, ppc64le, aarch64

With change:

  --base-arch BASE_ARCH
                        The base architecture. Default is same as host.
                        Allowed values: x86_64, ppc64le, aarch64

Change-Id: I53a4edf943a048f8659c71081abcd6dc22809316

commit_message:
Remove mox3 dependencies

Dependency for mox3 is fully removed. So this patch removes mox3
dependency from followings:

- lower-constraints.txt
- test-requirements.txt
- doc/requirements.txt

This should be cherry-picked into stable/rocky branch.

Change-Id: Idd1f095b5f7ae6a4b07153dd7d3587dc18822df6

revisions:
[{'created': '2018-08-22 01:34:32.000000000', 'message': 'import zuul job settings from project-config

This is a mechanically generated patch to complete step 1 of moving
the zuul job settings out of project-config and into each project
repository.

Because there will be a separate patch on each branch, the branch
specifiers for branch-specific jobs have been removed.

Because this patch is generated by a script, there may be some
cosmetic changes to the layout of the YAML file(s) as the contents are

commit_message:
import zuul job settings from project-config

This is a mechanically generated patch to complete step 1 of moving
the zuul job settings out of project-config and into each project
repository.

Because there will be a separate patch on each branch, the branch
specifiers for branch-specific jobs have been removed.

Because this patch is generated by a script, there may be some
cosmetic changes to the layout of the YAML file(s) as the contents are
normalized.

See the python3-first goal document for details:
https://governance.openstack.org/tc/goals/stein/python3-first.html

Change-Id: I2d5891157cc93f3b37872098c88f69efab594190
Story: #2002586
Task: #24341

commit_message:
Add always tag to systemd version task

The systemd version task requires an always tag to ensure it runs no
matter the tags provided on the CLI. If a deployer runs the role with
tags and this tag is not set the prep include task file will fail to
load.

Change-Id: Ic513225cdbd0f9fb49e61d499ab5e1ad5577caa5
Signed-off-by: Kevin Carter <kevin.carter@rackspace.com>

commit_message:
Add ensure_lbaas_package to neutron::server

Adds a new parameter ensure_lbaas_package same as for the other
service provider plugins. This can be used to only install the
LBaaS package and not the agents so that the neutron-server can
load the plugin.

Change-Id: I7f074fe3f8d3935d18f640de0d8a256f39ea8b11
(cherry picked from commit c70e4fa7f29c4ea183e3dd8f54549a6a0643307b)

commit_message:
Add ensure_lbaas_package to neutron::server

Adds a new parameter ensure_lbaas_package same as for the other
service provider plugins. This can be used to only install the
LBaaS package and not the agents so that the neutron-server can
load the plugin.

Change-Id: I7f074fe3f8d3935d18f640de0d8a256f39ea8b11

[{'created': '2018-08-29 00:44:56.000000000', 'message': 'Retry on MessagingTimeout to init compute RPC API during n-cpu start

When [upgrade_levels]/compute=auto, the RPC ComputeAPI client
gets the minimum nova-compute service version to determine the
RPC API pin version. This requires a roundtrip to conductor. If
nova-compute and conductor are starting around the same time, like
we see in our CI jobs, the call to conductor can hit an RPC
MessagingTimeout and kill the nova-compute service.

This change does two things:

1. Moves the RPC ComputeAPI client initialization to a bit
   later in the nova-compute service startup routine. Note
   that post_start_hook still runs before the service is
   joined to the service group in the service group API.

2. Adds a retry decorator which will retry two for a total
   of three attempts to init the compute RPC API client. Failing
   that, nova-compute will still fail to start as before.

Change-Id: I6dc9bccbd51d7c3cdf3924cc41d87c2ee3f934b3

commit_message:
Retry on MessagingTimeout to init compute RPC API during n-cpu start

When [upgrade_levels]/compute=auto, the RPC ComputeAPI client
gets the minimum nova-compute service version to determine the
RPC API pin version. This requires a roundtrip to conductor. If
nova-compute and conductor are starting around the same time, like
we see in our CI jobs, the call to conductor can hit an RPC
MessagingTimeout and kill the nova-compute service.

This change does two things:

1. Moves the RPC ComputeAPI client initialization to a bit
   later in the nova-compute service startup routine. Note
   that post_start_hook still runs before the service is
   joined to the service group in the service group API.

2. Adds a retry decorator which will retry for a total
   of three attempts to init the compute RPC API client. Failing
   that, nova-compute will still fail to start as before.

Change-Id: I6dc9bccbd51d7c3cdf3924cc41d87c2ee3f934b3
Closes-Bug: #1789484

commit_message:
FWaaS v2 dashbaord: clean up unnecessary get_dict() methods

APIDictWrapper provides to_dict() method, so there is no need
to have get_dict() method in Firewall wrapper API classes.

firewalls_v2.views.RouterCommonView is also unnecessary
as this is not used anywhere.

Change-Id: I760d653aa2404f574755572a90bfcd2bbad9a7bf
Closes-Bug: #1723951

[{'created': '2018-08-23 13:15:37.000000000', 'message': 'import zuul job settings from project-config

This is a mechanically generated patch to complete step 1 of moving
the zuul job settings out of project-config and into each project
repository.

Because there will be a separate patch on each branch, the branch
specifiers for branch-specific jobs have been removed.

Because this patch is generated by a script, there may be some
cosmetic changes to the layout of the YAML file(s) as the contents are
normalized.

commit_message:
import zuul job settings from project-config

This is a mechanically generated patch to complete step 1 of moving
the zuul job settings out of project-config and into each project
repository.

Because there will be a separate patch on each branch, the branch
specifiers for branch-specific jobs have been removed.

Because this patch is generated by a script, there may be some
cosmetic changes to the layout of the YAML file(s) as the contents are
normalized.

See the python3-first goal document for details:
https://governance.openstack.org/tc/goals/stein/python3-first.html

Depends-On: https://review.openstack.org/#/c/595921/
Change-Id: I8a4fe9c5ff93b19e65405e4f4a334009bafdbb0d
Story: #2002586
Task: #24316

commit_message:
check bulk port for binding data

There was a bug that prevented the post_op data to be included in the
bulk operations. This test will prevent regressing on it.

Depends-On: I7221f8050cff12f02f39cd8b13db735ab0dd92d4

Pass in rndc key to Designate deployment

We can't let puppet generate the key because then we end up with a
different key on each system and they can't talk to each other.

commit_message:
Open designate-mdns ports in firewall

For ha this is necessary so BIND servers on other nodes can request
zone transfers from mdns services that aren't on their local system.

Change-Id: Ia87be3b94eebedccadec2b2ff6d2687dcfb9d87a

commit_message:
Remove uneececary conditionals in network-environment jinja

In the environment/network-environment*.yaml files the
itaration is done only on networks that is enabled.

We do not need conditionals inside the loop to check
wheather the network is enabled or not.

Change-Id: I621c205aebcdb353ac487a5804bbe83fbc20c95d

(2 comments)

I have a concern that you can't take a non-production cryptographic provider and turn it into a production-quality solution by changing the way it's master key is stored... We should probably, at the very least, extend the Barbican threat analysis to include a close look at the SimpleCryptoPlugin."}, {'account_id': 18462, 'date': '2017-02-10 00:07:31.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2:

(4 comments)

A well written spec, I have a few questions. Kindly review.'}, {'account_id': 18462, 'date': '2017-02-10 00:09:11.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 2:

One of the questions got repeated, kindly ignore that.. gerrit was unresponsive..Also, I agree with Robert's comment on extending threat analysis of Barbican to the SimpleCryptoPlugin as well."}, {'account_id': 18462, 'date': '2017-02-14 16:12:05.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2: Code-Review-1'}, {'account_id': 7973, 'date': '2017-02-21 20:36:24.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2:

(11 comments)

@Rob, I understand your concern.  I guess by "production-ready" what I really want is a software-only solution that is good enough for someone who does not have very high security requirements (e.g. doesn't want to spend money on security).  I don't expect to achieve the same level of security that an HSM driver can provide.

I agree that the Barbican Threat Analysis should include SimpleCrypto (or a separate plugin that implements this spec).  I'd love to help to get an online threat analysis done after the PTG.

Thanks for the reviews, y'all!'}, {'account_id': 7973, 'date': '2017-02-21 20:37:02.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 3.'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2017-02-21 20:44:02.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3: Verified+1

Enhance SimpleCryptoPlugin

This spec proposes an enhancement to SimpleCryptoPlugin to remove the
encryption key from the barbican.conf file.

commit_message:
import zuul job settings from project-config

This is a mechanically generated patch to complete step 1 of moving
the zuul job settings out of project-config and into each project
repository.

Because there will be a separate patch on each branch, the branch
specifiers for branch-specific jobs have been removed.

Because this patch is generated by a script, there may be some
cosmetic changes to the layout of the YAML file(s) as the contents are
normalized.

See the python3-first goal document for details:
https://governance.openstack.org/tc/goals/stein/python3-first.html

Change-Id: I3bfa57c817c92684044859b80786d37a55d66283
Story: #2002586
Task: #24304

commit_message:
bump ansible from 2.5.5 to 2.5.8

Avoids pause module exception with redirected console.

See: https://github.com/ansible/ansible/issues/41717

Pausing for 30 seconds
(ctrl+C then 'C' = continue early, ctrl+C then 'A' = abort)
An exception occurred during task execution. To see the full traceback,
use -vvv. The error was: error: (25, 'Inappropriate ioctl for device')

Change-Id: I6914bf623deda0d257ba6a2f56b4e220a7931e06

[{'created': '2018-08-27 17:54:01.000000000', 'message': 'Filter args dict in JSONFormatter

In most formatters, any unused keys in the args dict will just be
discarded.  Because JSONFormatter logged the entire dict in addition
to the message, some values were included in the output that may
not have been intended.  This could include sensitive data, so we
should stop that.

In the interest of maintaining compatibility with any tools that are
reading the args dict, we leave the dict but filter out any unused
keys.

Change-Id: Ib64837c1ae93a27bef3d30a776320a373f18dd1c
Closes-Bug: 1571714
Closes-Bug: 1787214
'}]
commit_message:
Filter args dict in JSONFormatter

In most formatters, any unused keys in the args dict will just be
discarded.  Because JSONFormatter logged the entire dict in addition
to the message, some values were included in the output that may
not have been intended.  This could include sensitive data, so we
should stop that.

In the interest of maintaining compatibility with any tools that are
reading the args dict, we leave the dict but filter out any unused
keys.

Change-Id: Ib64837c1ae93a27bef3d30a776320a373f18dd1c
Closes-Bug: 1571714
Closes-Bug: 1787214

commit_message:
import zuul job settings from project-config

This is a mechanically generated patch to complete step 1 of moving
the zuul job settings out of project-config and into each project
repository.

Because there will be a separate patch on each branch, the branch
specifiers for branch-specific jobs have been removed.

Because this patch is generated by a script, there may be some
cosmetic changes to the layout of the YAML file(s) as the contents are
normalized.

See the python3-first goal document for details:
https://governance.openstack.org/tc/goals/stein/python3-first.html

Change-Id: Iec514e7a4ba23c885d3e956632a635a89e6a4229
Story: #2002586
Task: #24341

commit_message:
SIO: Clean up padded volume comments

There were a couple of spots still referring specifically to thick
provisioned volumes as being an issue without padding enabled. This is
an issue regardless of provisioning type, so this cleans up those
mentions.

commit_message:
import zuul job settings from project-config

This is a mechanically generated patch to complete step 1 of moving
the zuul job settings out of project-config and into each project
repository.

Because there will be a separate patch on each branch, the branch
specifiers for branch-specific jobs have been removed.

Because this patch is generated by a script, there may be some
cosmetic changes to the layout of the YAML file(s) as the contents are
normalized.

See the python3-first goal document for details:
https://governance.openstack.org/tc/goals/stein/python3-first.html

commit_message:
Use mirrored etcd container for openshift CI

We need to use the fedora etcd container for openshift, because we
require the default user to be root[1]. However, this registry is not
mirrored in openstack infra, so we end up getting timeouts. The
fedora container has been manually copied into our docker.io registry
which is mirrored and will not have the same timeout issues.

[1] https://review.openstack.org/576497

Depends-On: I48fcbcfba5e8b41f28e23773e2cc02229f7eee7d
Depends-On: I8e6bc6d46a32a55098991e1916cedebb7e0b5c93
Change-Id: Idfbaf756c49957219ab1f526a2666b43aaddce8b

commit_message:
Amendment of the agent http provisioning spec

During spec[0] implementation, there are several findings related to
performance. This patch updates the image conversion rule to avoid
the situation when stream_raw_images and force_raw_images are both set
to true. Some descriptive text are added with regards to the options
that may affect performance.

[0] http://specs.openstack.org/openstack/ironic-specs/specs/not-implemented/agent-http-provisioning.html

Change-Id: I26179155f613e0bb694aa202094e0c52c0528131
Story: #1598852
Task: #10474

commit_message:
DVR: Add IPv6 csnat port address correctly

If router gateway info update, in l3_dvr_db will receive events,
We will get subnets from router attached DVR port, if exists
multiple IPv6 slaac-enabled subnets, previous code will create
csnat port form one of the IPv6 subnets.
This is inconsistency with router interface
udpate in _update_snat_v6_addrs_after_intf_update.

This patch adds all IPv6 subnets if the distributed
router port have multiple IPv6 subnets.

Change-Id: I02ffed238897ebc91b96aebb7f94ed90b7613769
Closes-Bug: #1786169

commit_message:
Move rocky implemented specs

This moves the completed rocky specs to the implemented
directory, adds the redirects and also removes the rocky-template
symlink from the approved directory and docs.

This was done using:

  $ tox -e move-implemented-specs -- rocky

Change-Id: I298d6d106f392b662930be97bf88637f1056c0d8

commit_message:
Save and verify allocation and inventory values for nova/placement

This makes the nova resources module save information about the host
inventory (first node only), as well as the allocation information
about the test instance before the upgrade. Afterwards in the
verify phase, we compare those values to the current ones to make
sure we have not lost or changed anything during the upgrade.

Change-Id: Ifef2acf7dce17d0fa21baac9da6f8403e69136a4

commit_message:
import zuul job settings from project-config

This is a mechanically generated patch to complete step 1 of moving
the zuul job settings out of project-config and into each project
repository.

Because there will be a separate patch on each branch, the branch
specifiers for branch-specific jobs have been removed.

Because this patch is generated by a script, there may be some
cosmetic changes to the layout of the YAML file(s) as the contents are
normalized.

See the python3-first goal document for details:
https://governance.openstack.org/tc/goals/stein/python3-first.html

Change-Id: I66712ed925e07ee3032605790f324a35e0ed46a3
Story: #2002586
Task: #24314

Update status to active when locations replaced

Image status should be changed from 'queued' to 'active' when
'locations' has been successfully replaced.

Closes-Bug: 1750892

There was also the upgrade scenario Dan mentioned in IRC, which is you're upgrading a node that has a resized instance on it before the resize is confirmed, so the source node is old and the dest node is new. commit_message:
Report client: get_allocations_for_provider_tree

The reshaper path needs to pass all the allocations related to the
compute node's provider tree to update_provider_tree so it can shuffle
those allocations appropriately. This patch adds a new
get_allocations_for_provider_tree method to the report client for this
purpose.

Blueprint: reshape-provider-tree

Change-Id: I73811f3e3bf19dec3a240e1f1f8c69f4c98d677c

commit_message:
Fix incorrect log resources querying

This patch aims to fix a co-existence problem between security_group
and firewall_group log resources due to incorrect log querying from
database.

Change-Id: Ic60ad436e0fbb23cdae0e63eaeb73130ebf02089
Closes-Bug: #1787119

[{'account_id': 14070, 'date': '2018-08-24 22:07:44.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 1.'}, {'account_id': 14070, 'date': '2018-08-24 22:20:23.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

Note to reviewers: I locally rebased the whole reshaper series on top of this and ran all the tests. Everything passed.

I don't know if it's really expensive to do it this way because we have to calculate the hash every time; or if we can wind up with duplicates somehow (same provider, but with a different subset of fields filled in?); or if we care about any of that. If so I suppose the alternative would be to create a separate dict with the objects and pass it in as an additional arg."}, {'account_id': 23498, 'date': '2018-08-24 23:56:45.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

++ turned out to simplify the code and make it more readable anyway. nice work, Eric.'}, {'account_id': 9708, 'date': '2018-08-28 14:52:43.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 2: Code-Review+2 Workflow+1

> Note to reviewers: I locally rebased the whole reshaper series on
 > top of this and ran all the tests. Everything passed.
 > 
 > I don't know if it's really expensive to do it this way because we
 > have to calculate the hash every time; or if we can wind up with
 > duplicates somehow (same provider, but with a different subset of
 > fields filled in?); or if we care about any of that. If so I
 > suppose the alternative would be to create a separate dict with the
 > objects and pass it in as an additional arg.

As I see there are no explicit hash function is defined for ovos. So based on the python doc [1], the hash of the ovos will be based on the id of the ovo. So every ResourceProvider instance will have different hash value. This means if the same RP is read from the db by rpuuid twice the hash of the resulting ResourceProvider objects would different.

Fortunately the inventory part of the schema is built in a way that every RP mentioned there only once. Therefore the handler code will create one ResourceProvider object for every rpuuid. So there won't be duplicates in the dict passed forward.

As hashing only depends on the id() of the object by default calculating hash is not expensive.

commit_message:
Fix race condition in reshaper handler

Fix the race condition identified at [1] by indexing the `inventories`
argument to the resource_provider.reshape method by ResourceProvider
object rather than its UUID. That means we never have to do a fresh
lookup for the provider.

[1] https://review.openstack.org/#/c/585033/18/nova/api/openstack/placement/objects/resource_provider.py@4195

Change-Id: Ie21bddc186364db2b10af45546c35b9ad5a0208b

commit_message:
Explicitly link to the HTTP RFCs

In the opening we advise people to use the HTTP RFCs as the ultimate
authority but do not link to them. This change adds the links and
generalizes the warning to the entirety of the guidelines, not just
to non-JSON apis.

Change-Id: I40a59594a477d6802a16d8b0ca11020629eff292

commit_message:
import zuul job settings from project-config

This is a mechanically generated patch to complete step 1 of moving
the zuul job settings out of project-config and into each project
repository.

Because there will be a separate patch on each branch, the branch
specifiers for branch-specific jobs have been removed.

Because this patch is generated by a script, there may be some
cosmetic changes to the layout of the YAML file(s) as the contents are
normalized.

See the python3-first goal document for details:
https://governance.openstack.org/tc/goals/stein/python3-first.html

Change-Id: I59f4cbc0a21b8be3a1cae28a64f90d5adcf6be24
Story: #2002586
Task: #24337

commit_message:
skipping nova driver tests for queens

because congress nova driver in queens does not work with the new
novaclient 10.1.0 now part of upper-constraints
due to https://review.openstack.org/#/c/571540/

Depends-On: https://review.openstack.org/#/c/595884/
Change-Id: I898b37dd3ffbd519d97b499785f4405b8703dac7

commit_message:
Add OctaviaEventStreamerDriver and change default

octavia::health_manager::event_streamer_driver is forcely set to
'queue_event_streamer' with no option to change it. The event streamer
specifies which driver to use for syncing Octavia and Neutron LBaaS
databases. It is highly recommended to disable if one doesn't need to
sync the database or is running Octavia in standalone mode by setting
event_streamer_driver to noop_event_streamer.

Change-Id: I400ce9a059aba195cdd987ba51360ef3d7f258f3
Closes-Bug: #1787608

commit_message:
Switch to workflow driven image prepare

This tests container-prepare-workflow and concludes the coding/testing
portion of this blueprint.

Since image prepare happens during overcloud deploy, the role
overcloud-prep-containers is skipped completely from rocky onwards.
The file containers-prepare-parameter.yaml is written out during
undercloud-deploy.

Change-Id: I006e48754ed1710ae8cc6e9c1d35e9c2e66b5907

commit_message:
Update plans state management

Reorganize plans fetching into separate actions which are
separately invoked when needed PlansList lists the plans, PlanCard
loads plan details - plan-environment.yaml to fetch the description.
Plans store is reorganized apropriately, this leads to simpler
reducer as there are no collisions between plans and plan details
loading.

Prepare EditPlan and EditPlanForm as plan editting is currently
broken, the form is going to be fixed in subsequent patch

Plans transitions are handled as a List of transitions

When plan is created, it is automatically added to plans list
and newly mounted PlanCard takes care of fetching the details.
No plans refetch is required

Story: 2003188
Task: 23338
Change-Id: Ie4c1fc256bbe3243e07edb03d7c60804016d52bd
(cherry picked from commit 91b9fbdf76c2712679fb9a6c11eba17d9e943480)

in the application, plan form is now ready to be expanded to include

commit_message:
List deployment plan in nodes list for deployed nodes

* Fetch Stacks on initial load to populate data for available
  nodes counts
* Separate stack outputs into a separate section in stacks
  state to avoid outputs getting removed in case when stacks in
  fetchStacksSuccess action does not include it. (case for stacks
  comming from zaqar message)
* Fetch stacks on Nodes component
* Add selectors to get server ids from stack outputs by stack
* Update nodes selector to include PlanName identified from server
  ids and nodes instance_uuid

Story: 2003385
Task: 24460
Change-Id: I3fe6ba8256e8d983d121549209aaf4b89eb91fbd

commit_message:
Remove deprecated ironic command from prep images

We're still using ironic to list baremetal nodes, but this was
deprecated and so we need to re adapt all the commands to the new way
using "openstack baremetal node" command, which will be also retro
compatible. This commit addresses all this stuff in the prep image
template.

Change-Id: Ie0aeffffcf044abd03b495e9debd8ee766eb5628

commit_message:
Create missing directories before mounting them

When deploying with podman, we need to create directories if they don't
exist before trying to mount them later when containers are starting.
Otherwise, podman fails with this kind of error:
error checking path \"/etc/iscsi\": stat /etc/iscsi: no such file or directory"

Change-Id: I7dbdc7f3646dda99c8014b4c8ca2edd48778b392
